## Hommie App - Environment Variables
## Create a file named `.env` in this same folder and copy these lines, then fill in values.
## After editing `.env`, restart Expo with: `npm start -- --clear`

# --- Supabase (optional) ---
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key

# --- Paystack (Payment Processing) ---
EXPO_PUBLIC_PAYSTACK_PUBLIC_KEY=pk_test_your_paystack_public_key

# --- Paystack Server (required for REAL payments) ---
# Paystack transaction initialization must run server-side using PAYSTACK_SECRET_KEY.
# Point this to your backend (e.g. the admin-dashboard Next.js server):
# Example (local): http://localhost:3000
# Example (Expo on phone): http://YOUR_COMPUTER_LAN_IP:3000
EXPO_PUBLIC_PAYSTACK_BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:3000